<subSubSection id="16FF34B93B66A17002C7D645060F5448" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="1694" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="5E5A67323B66A17102C7D6450646532F" blockId="36.[178,638,1369,1391]" box="[178,638,1369,1391]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
<typeStatus id="815ED9903B66A17102C7D645052C532F" box="[178,276,1369,1391]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">Holotype</typeStatus>
. figs 188-193. Body size: 
<quantity id="991DCAD73B66A1710068D6450642532F" box="[541,634,1369,1391]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E5A67323B66A17102C7D663073753AC" blockId="36.[178,1085,1407,1516]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
Black. Pale yellow: the whole of clypeus but semitransparent ventral edge; subapical 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A17102C7D68004E153F2" bold="true" box="[178,217,1436,1458]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">Tsa</emphasis>
; apical palpi; two lateral subapical stripes on 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A17100B6D68006E553F4" bold="true" box="[707,733,1436,1460]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
N 
<subScript id="C26165773B66A17100A0D6BA06E553F4" attach="left" box="[725,733,1446,1460]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
disk; half tegula; most of 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A171018FD680000E53F4" bold="true" box="[1018,1078,1436,1460]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
LaSt 
<subScript id="C26165773B66A171065BD6BA000E53F4" attach="left" box="[1070,1078,1446,1460]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
; ventral surface of coxae, tarsi and most of legs; narrow apical stripe on 1st to 6 
<superScript id="A990CA7A3B66A171019BD6AF07C25381" attach="left" box="[1006,1018,1459,1473]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">th</superScript>
terga; two lateral apical stripes on 2 
<superScript id="A990CA7A3B66A17103AED6CD05D3539F" attach="left" box="[475,491,1489,1503]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">nd</superScript>
to 6 
<superScript id="A990CA7A3B66A171006DD6CD061C539F" attach="left" box="[536,548,1489,1503]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">th</superScript>
sterna. Wings hyaline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E5A67323B66A17002C7D6E0057A57C3" blockId="36.[178,1085,1532,1585]" lastBlockId="37.[178,1086,213,387]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="1694" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A17102C7D6E004DA5052" bold="true" box="[178,226,1532,1554]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">PoG</emphasis>
about half 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A171032ED6E005B35052" bold="true" box="[347,395,1532,1554]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">FoO</emphasis>
. Mid flagellomeri with a ratio 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A17100A7D6E006DB5052" bold="true" box="[722,739,1532,1554]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">L</emphasis>
/ 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A171009FD6E007355052" bold="true" box="[746,781,1532,1554]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">LA</emphasis>
mor than 2.4. No keel along fore border neither tooth on antero ventral corner of 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A17100A2D50506C95071" bold="true" box="[727,753,1561,1585]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
N 
<subScript id="C26165773B66A171009CD53F06C95071" attach="left" box="[745,753,1571,1585]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
disk. 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B66A1710147D50507585071" bold="true" box="[818,864,1561,1585]" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">
Em 
<subScript id="C26165773B66A171012DD53F07585071" attach="left" box="[856,864,1571,1585]" fontSize="6" pageId="36" pageNumber="1693">3</subScript>
</emphasis>
with strong wrinkles along the 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B67A1700362D3C6057356B0" bold="true" box="[279,331,218,240]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">smm</emphasis>
. Hind femur with a distinct ventral longitudinal lamella apically. 1 
<superScript id="A990CA7A3B67A1700182D3C9003A56A3" attach="left" box="[1015,1026,213,227]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">st</superScript>
to 5 
<superScript id="A990CA7A3B67A1700644D3C9000556A3" attach="none" box="[1073,1085,213,227]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">th</superScript>
tergal surfaes bipunctate by sparse large 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B67A1700011D3E4064A574E" bold="true" box="[612,626,248,270]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">p</emphasis>
among very small 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B67A1700136D3E40769574E" bold="true" box="[835,849,248,270]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">p</emphasis>
. Epipygium short and prominent upon the remainder of 7 
<superScript id="A990CA7A3B67A170005FD213060E575D" attach="left" box="[554,566,271,285]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">th</superScript>
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B67A1700037D2090666576B" bold="true" box="[578,606,277,299]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">Te</emphasis>
with very shallow median notch. Very long dense hair (longer than mid flagellomeri) on most of head and mesosoma, covering underlying integument on clypeus, frons, pronotal disk, 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B67A170009FD24C07355728" bold="true" box="[746,781,336,360]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">
Es 
<subScript id="C26165773B67A1700170D24607355728" attach="left" box="[773,781,346,360]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B67A170016FD24C07055728" bold="true" box="[794,829,336,360]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">
Es 
<subScript id="C26165773B67A1700140D24607055728" attach="left" box="[821,829,346,360]" fontSize="6" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="6C91BB203B67A170011BD24C07455726" bold="true" box="[878,893,336,358]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">P</emphasis>
. Long hair also on tergal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E5A67323B67A17002C7D28F05015785" blockId="37.[178,1086,402,453]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">N o t e. Distinct by the dense long hair on head and mesosoma and very narrow gonosquama.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E5A67323B67A17002C7D2C9060F5448" blockId="37.[178,1085,469,520]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1694">Derivatio nominis. From the Greek words ȑȡȚȠȞ = wool and ıȫμĮ = body because of the dense hair on the head and mesosoma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
